                        <item xml:id="e1">- Crude copy of part of Ps. 1 and incipit of Text 1 (writing exercise?) on fol. 1v.&#xD;
- Passage of text or note have been effaced on fols. 2rc, 101vb.&#xD;
- Writing exercise of Ethiopic fidäl: fols. 2r, 102r, 103r.&#xD;
- Minor notes and writing exercises: fols. 2r, 7v, 9v, 29v, 32r, 48v, 78r, 105r.&#xD;
- Notes in the upper margins referring to the content or the section of the text: fols. 4v, 11r, 14r, 15v, 17v, 20v, 24v, 26r, 30v, 32r-v, 33r, 37v, 38r (bottom, by pen), 39v, 41r-v, 42r-v, 43r, 46v, 48v, 49r, 50v, 52v (bottom, by pen), 54r, 55r, 57r, 58r, 59v, 62r, 63r, 64v, 66r, 68r, 69v, 70r, 71r, 72r, 73r, 79v, 80r-v, 81r-v, 83r (by pen), 90r, 91v, 92v, 93r.&#xD;
- Corrections written interlineally: fols. 23va, 61vb.&#xD;
- A crude note in faded ink, mentioning a certain Gäbrä Giyorgis, on fol. 102r.&#xD;
- A note mentioning Bet Maryam as the owner of the manuscript on fol. 101vb. &#xD;
- Drawing exercise on fols. 102v, 103r, 104r, 105v.</item>
